imdb.title: Cardcaptor Sakura Clear Card-hen
imdb.plot: Cardcaptor Sakura: Clear Card starts at the point where Cardcaptor Sakura ends, when Sakura Kinomoto starts junior high school alongside her friends, including her new boyfriend Syaoran, who had just returned to Tomoeda. After hav...

episodes.title: Sakura and the Clear Cards
episodes.plot: It's April, the cherry trees are in full bloom, and Sakura has entered Tomoeda Middle School. She's reunited with Syaoran, who has returned from Hong Kong, and her new student life has begun.

episodes.title: Sakura and the Room with No Exit
episodes.plot: It's the new term, and the hot topic at school is clubs! Sakura and Tomoyo decide to join the same clubs they did in elementary school: cheerleading and chorus.

episodes.title: Sakura's Heavy Rain Alert
episodes.plot: It's been raining buckets all day. Sakura and Tomoyo take shelter in a park on the way home from school, and suddenly the Key of Dreams at Sakura's chest begins to shine... Is it the work of a card?

episodes.title: Sakura and the Lovely Transfer Student
episodes.plot: A new transfer student named Akiho Shinomoto joins Sakura's class. She's just arrived in Japan after living overseas, so her Japanese is still very stiff and formal. Sakura invites her to eat lunch with her group, excited to make a new friend.

episodes.title: Sakura Feels a Pull at the Flower Viewing
episodes.plot: Sakura is having a flower-viewing party with her friends Tomoyo, Syaoran, Chiharu, Naoko, and Yamazaki, as well as the new transfer student Akiho.

episodes.title: Sakura, the Rabbit and the Song of the Moon
episodes.plot: Sakura continues to face the hooded figure in her dreams. At school, everyone says they want to hear Akiho sing again after being charmed by her voice at their flower-viewing party, so they meet in the music room after classes are over.

episodes.title: Sakura and a Game of Tag in the Garden
episodes.plot: Sakura and Kero-chan visit Tomoyo's house to test the abilities of the Record card. Tomoyo's mother appears and gives Sakura an enthusiastic welcome, then the girls head outside to test the card.

episodes.title: Sakura, the Clock, and a Hide-and-Seek Game
episodes.plot: Sakura finds out that Akiho has moved into the mansion formerly inhabited by Clow Reed's reincarnation, Eriol. She pays a visit with Tomoyo and meets Kaito, the butler who's been taking care of Akiho since her childhood.

episodes.title: Sakura's Thrilling Aquarium Visit
episodes.plot: Sakura invites Syaoran out for the day with tickets given to her by her father. She's worked hard on the rolled omelets for their lunch, and now they make their way to the aquarium Sakura visited when she captured the Clow Card, Watery.

episodes.title: Sakura and the Sleep Labyrinth
episodes.plot: Akiho pays a visit to Sakura's house one evening while her father and brother are both away. They look at Sakura's elementary school pictures and have dinner together, but then Akiho suddenly falls asleep.

episodes.title: Sakura and the Upside-Down Penguin
episodes.plot: Syaoran meets Kaito through a chance encounter on the way home from school. He informs Eriol, whom he's beem secretly keeping in touch with, and they both begin to suspect Kaito is a very powerful magician.

episodes.title: Sakura and the Ice Ball Game Tournament
episodes.plot: Sakura and her friends participate in an after-school sports tournament. However, a sudden snowstorm rages that is the work of the "Hail" card.

episodes.title: Sakura and Welcome Back, Meiling
episodes.plot: Sakura is overjoyed to see Syaoran's cousin, Meiling, make an unannounced visit from Hong Kong. Meiling asks to stay at Sakura's house, so they head straight there. Meanwhile, the power Toya lost by giving it to Yukito is gradually starting to return.

episodes.title: Sakura, the Shrine and the Zoo?
episodes.plot: Sakura is visiting the Tsukimine Shrine market with Meiling, Akiho, and the rest of their friends. She enjoys a day of browsing the many shops and stalls on the grounds along with Akiho, who's never seen a Japanese shrine before.

episodes.title: Sakura's Nostalgic Viewing Party
episodes.plot: Meiling, Sakura, and Syaoran meet up at Sakura's house where they encourage Syaoran to get more rest. Later, at Tomoyo's house, the group watches some home movies when the earth starts shaking.

episodes.title: Sakura and Meiling's Friend
episodes.plot: Sakura manages to capture the card that showed up at Tomoyo's house, but her relief is short-lived. As they're returning home, Sakura and Meiling are suddenly attacked by a mysterious girl in the road!

episodes.title: Sakura and the Crazy Sweets
episodes.plot: Today is the cooking lesson in home ec class that everyone's been looking forward to. Sakura's morning is thrown into a panic when she forgets her apron, but she and her friends are excited to make roll cakes in class.

episodes.title: Sakura and the Fire and Water Birds
episodes.plot: When Sakura senses a card late at night, she heads to Tsukimine Shrine with Kero-chan, Tomoyo, and Syaoran.

episodes.title: Sakura and Akiho's Lullaby
episodes.plot: Sakura and Akiho perform a reading of a children's story. Sakura had used the power of a card to record the event, but she notices something odd when she replays the footage.

episodes.title: Sakura, Rainbows, and Grandpa
episodes.plot: Sakura is spending her Sunday morning making rolled omelets for the homemade lunches she's taking for her outing with Syaoran.

episodes.title: Sakura, the Mirror and the Key of Memories
episodes.plot: Cerberus and Yue meet with Eriol via magic to discuss Sakura's new cards. Eriol has found out that Kaito took something from the magic association he once belonged to, but at that moment, Kaito's magic severs the trio's communication link.

episodes.title: Sakura's Clear Cards
episodes.plot: Eriol orders Yue and Kero to keep a secret about Akiho and Kaito from Sakura. Despite their reservations, they do so as the cloaked figure appears before Sakura once again.
